â€œHis health is the most important thing, so we want him to be healthy when he does come back,â€ Stubblefield said. â€œWe don't want him rushing back and then he re-aggravates the injury. So we would rather he comes back 100 percent.â€

â€œOur biggest and best memories of being here are winning the national championship,â€ Hart said.
Hart spent his first two NBA seasons with the Lakers and is in his third season with the Pelicans. Heâ€™s averaging a career-best 13.1 points, with 7.5 rebounds in 35 games.
Wright had noticed Hart on a scouting trip for another player and quickly became enamored with a player he says he knew would be a â€œgreat Villanova basketball player.â€
